            <li>Ask for treatment-specific case studies and written timelines before signing any contract</li>
            <li>Boutique Miami firms often deliver faster, hands-on service than enterprise agencies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>How We Evaluated These 13 Agencies</h2>

        <p>We identified these firms through Google search for "med spa SEO agency," review aggregators like Clutch, public pricing pages, and agency portfolios. For local Miami agencies, we verified through business registrations and client references. Thryv is included as the publisher of this guide, meeting the Lanham Act disclosure standard for commercial comparison content.</p>

        <p>Each profile is factual. We've included what agencies publicly claim about their services, experience, and pricing. We've avoided speculation about comparative quality or capability gaps. You'll find those answers in discovery calls and client references, not in a guide.</p>

        <h2>National vs Local Miami Med Spa SEO Agencies: What's the Trade-Off?</h2>

        <p>National agencies bring established playbooks, larger teams, and experience across multiple markets. They're built for scale and often require 6 to 12-month contracts. Costs run higher. You get a team rather than a single point of contact.</p>

        <p>Local Miami agencies know the competitive landscape, neighborhood-by-neighborhood demand, and which keywords drive real traffic in your market. They typically offer shorter contract terms and more direct access to the person doing your work. Trade-off: they may not have experience outside Miami.</p>

        <p>Neither path is objectively better. Choose based on your budget, timeline, and whether you want a large support system or a hands-on local partner. For specific pricing benchmarks, see our <a href="/blog/med-spa-marketing-cost-miami/">guide to med spa marketing costs in Miami</a>.</p>

