        <h2>FAQ: Choosing a Med Spa SEO Agency</h2>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How much does med spa SEO cost in Miami?</summary>
          <p>Med spa SEO services range from $500 to $5,000+ per month depending on scope. Basic local SEO (Google Business Profile + keyword targeting) starts around $500. Full-service SEO with content, link building, and paid ads runs $2,000 to $5,000. Enterprise agencies often require 6 or 12-month contracts. Boutique local agencies in Miami typically cost less than national firms.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do med spa SEO agencies work with Google Ads?</summary>
          <p>Many do. Some agencies specialize in organic SEO only, while others offer a full-service suite including Google Ads, Facebook ads, and paid social. If you want SEO + paid media managed by one team, ask during your initial conversation. Bundling services can be cheaper than hiring two separate agencies, but only if both teams are equally strong.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What's the difference between a national med spa agency and a local Miami agency?</summary>
          <p>National agencies bring experience across many markets and larger teams. They often charge more and may require longer contracts. Local Miami agencies know the market, neighborhood nuances, and local competitors. They offer more hands-on service and flexibility. Neither is automatically better, it depends on your budget, timeline, and whether you want a large support team or a single point of contact.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long does med spa SEO take to show results?</summary>
          <p>Most agencies deliver early wins in 4 to 8 weeks. Quick wins often come from Google Business Profile optimization and local citations. Ranking for competitive keywords typically takes 3 to 6 months. Major traffic jumps often appear between months 4 and 8. Always ask your agency for a realistic timeline tied to your specific keywords before signing.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Should I hire an SEO agency or a freelance SEO consultant?</summary>
          <p>Agencies bring team depth, faster turnaround, and accountability through a company structure. Freelancers offer lower cost and often more direct access to the person doing the work. Agencies are better if you need content, ads, design, and SEO as a package. Freelancers work if you need SEO only and want to save money. Either way, look for documented case studies and references from med spas.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What questions should I ask a med spa SEO agency before hiring?</summary>
          <p>Ask: What's your experience with med spas specifically? Can you show case studies? What keywords will you target? How long are contracts? What's included in the monthly fee? How do you handle reporting? What happens if I'm not happy? Do you use white-hat SEO tactics? A good agency will give you clear, honest answers without hard-selling or making unrealistic promises.</p>
        </details>

